reviews.text: Rather like the station that time forgot, with a rather nice old canopy but the adjacent building, whilist still intact, has rather unsightly metal sheets over the windows. Trains to and from London run until fairly late at night, although itʼs not a place to linger after dark as the platform lights only appear to come on when a train is in present and there may be few, if any other passengers around. The atmosphere is, in fact, somewhat eerie and it would make a good setting for a murder mystery or ghost story!!

Probably one of the most basic stations you can find here next to Battlesbridge. No ticket office, a car park, a payphone and it feels like it's in the middle of nowhere. At least access is step free and the staff can sell you tickets if the machine isn't working.
